# $PROJECT_NAME — Cursor Rules

## Governance

### Three Laws (Non-Negotiable)
1. No remediation without a Work Order
2. No Work Order without an evidence-backed finding
3. No finding without investigation

### Work Order Protocol
- All work tracked in `docs/planning/WO-INDEX.md`
- Quality gate manifest stored at `quality-gate-manifest.json`
- Run `bash scripts/gate-runner.sh pre_commit` before committing
- Run `bash scripts/gate-runner.sh wo_exit` after completing a WO
- Reference WO number in commit messages: `feat(wo-NNN): description`

### Zero-Stub Policy
- No `NotImplementedError`, `pass`-only functions, empty implementations
- No `# TODO` or `# FIXME` in committed code
- If something can't be implemented fully, flag it as a blocker

## Security

### NEVER Do
- Hardcode secrets (API keys, tokens, passwords) in source code
- Use string formatting for SQL queries (use parameterized queries)
- Write to `.env` files programmatically
- Target production URLs in development commands
- Use `eval()`, `exec()`, or equivalent unsafe patterns
- Force push to any branch

### ALWAYS Do
- Store secrets in `.env` (gitignored) and access via environment variables
- Validate all external input at system boundaries
- Use established auth libraries for authentication
- Target staging environment for all development work

